<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-31T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-31T09:00:00-05:00" n="748" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3292: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-31T14:00:00+00:00">December 31, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received December 31—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>643. Department’s 401, December 30, 6 p.m.<note n="81" xml:id="d748fn1">Not printed.</note> Customs notice number
                                    361 was published and issued by the Commissioners of Customs and
                                    Excise on December 23, making arrangement with Yugoslavia
                                    effective, beginning December 24, pursuant to Order in Council,
                                    copy of which was forwarded to the Department in pouch of
                                    December 24th under cover of despatch 1884 of December
                                        24th.<note n="81" xml:id="d748fn2">Not printed.</note> No
                                    particular reaction given to our communication of December 24 to
                                    Foreign Office but it has been acknowledged with statement that
                                    subject matter thereof is under consideration. Copy of customs
                                    notice just received will be forwarded in next pouch.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>